			<title>RIFT 5 things to make a great game better</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?70811-5-things-to-make-a-great-game-better&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Fri, 04 Mar 2011 15:06:49 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[Straight up - I love Rift. It's the best MMO to be released since WoW, and it's occupying way too much of my timer. But it's not perfect, and there are just a few simple things that could be changed to improve it. 
 
i) Stop any level mob knock you off your mount. It's incredibly infuriating and...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<!-- BEGIN TEMPLATE: postbit_external -->
<div>Straight up - I love Rift. It's the best MMO to be released since WoW, and it's occupying way too much of my timer. But it's not perfect, and there are just a few simple things that could be changed to improve it.<br />
<br />
i) Stop any level mob knock you off your mount. It's incredibly infuriating and nonsense that my level 30 character will still get trampled on as he tries to cross Freemarch. It's just not fun being dismounted all the time by grey mobs. <br />
<br />
ii) Get rid of the stacking debuff from fleeing a fight / trying to run past a mob. This is a DREADFUL idea, and means I have to kill grey mobs for no purpose when dismounted. I honestly have no idea why this is in the game, other than to slow you down and piss you off. <br />
<br />
iii) Add in more graveyards. There just aren't enough - in any zone I've been in. Corpse runs are not fun once they take over a minute. I understand there may be a n issue with graveyward zerging a rift boss, but to be frank - that's happening anyway. Don't penalise everyone for it. <br />
<br />
iv) Add in more transportation. The zones need multiple portculum hubs between the outposts. Even Freemarch is cursed by having the planar goods saleperson in Kings Retreat and the bulk of the zone a mile to the south. (The Guardian starting zone has a portculum in it for exactly this reason - not sure why King's retreat doesn't have the same quest and gateway). Right now, the lack of transportation means that invasions often go wrong because no-one can reach the mobs in time, and it prevents players from getting too fights and content. (It's also a real pain doing your crafting dailies if your current adventuring area isn't near the portculum for that zone). <br />
<br />
v) Give players much more control over their buff &amp; debuff bars. As a rogue, I have 4 60 second buffs I need to keep running, plus a 20 second protection buff whilst tanking and a 30 second shield buff. There is no way for me to spot these other than manually track them in my buff bar - which is nigh on impossible given all the buffs we have. If you have a bard in your group, it's just flat out nightmare-ish. We need to be able to set it so we only see our own buffs in the buff bar, we need to be able to set it so short duration buffs (1 minute or less) can go elsewhere on the screen. <br />
<br />
And just for me - please fix the teleporting under the world bug as a Riftstalker. Its the best rogue class any MMO has ever introduced with that talent spec, and I love every minute playing it, but it's unbelievably annoying and frustrtaing to have to run back from the graveyard every so often because you were fighting on a slope, or the moon is half gibeous or whatever causes it.</div>

 
<!-- END TEMPLATE: postbit_external -->]]></content:encoded>
