			<title>RIFT A few questions</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?70771-A-few-questions&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Mon, 28 Feb 2011 20:49:07 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[I have a few questions if anyone doesn't mind answering. 
 
How are the system requirements?  I have an Athlon 64 x2 4600+, GeForce 8600 GTS, and 4gb of ram.  I've read that the minimum requirements are extremely low, like a dual core 2ghz and an old GeForce FX 5900, but in my experience minimum...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<!-- BEGIN TEMPLATE: postbit_external -->
<div>I have a few questions if anyone doesn't mind answering.<br />
<br />
How are the system requirements?  I have an Athlon 64 x2 4600+, GeForce 8600 GTS, and 4gb of ram.  I've read that the minimum requirements are extremely low, like a dual core 2ghz and an old GeForce FX 5900, but in my experience minimum reqs are never actually playable.  I don't have to be able to run the game with everything turned up to the max, but I don't want it all turned all the way down either.  I need to be able to play with enough textures that you can make out facial features, a playable rendering distance, and reasonably little machine lag.  So any of you playing with an older rig have any insight on how the game might play for me?<br />
<br />
How much group content is there?<br />
<br />
How is the group content for leveling?  For an example of what I mean, in Everquest 2, xp in group dungeons was excellent pre-kunark.  I especially loved the Kingdom of Sky expansion because it had big long quest lines that took place almost entirely in group dungeons.  Leveling from 60-70 in KoS in eq2 was probably the most fun progressing I've had in an MMO.  By contrast I hated that with Kunark, it seemed all heroic content gave very minimal xp as compared to solo quests.  I have much less experience with WoW, but it 'felt' to be this way as well.  Very solo quest oriented when it came to leveling.  This was also my experience with Aion, Warhammer Online, etc. etc.<br />
<br />
I've been avoiding new games for a while because I won't be able to upgrade my PC anytime soon, but with the seemingly low system reqs for Rift, I might give it a try.<br />
<br />
Thanks for reading.<br />
<br />
- Aaraden</div>

 
